# Testing Patterns

## Unit Tests

- Test JSON Schema validators with valid and invalid inputs
- Test event handlers with mocked room state
- Test rate limiter with various event frequencies
- Use Jest or Mocha for test framework

## Integration Tests

- Use test harness (`scripts/test-harness.js`) to simulate multiple WebSocket clients
- Test message flow: client A sends EVENT → verify clients B/C receive STATE
- Test reconnection: disconnect and reconnect with same clientId → verify tombstone reattachment
- Test drift reconciliation: simulate client drift → verify server corrects clients

## Test Harness Patterns

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - simulate real client behavior
const client = await createTestClient();
await client.join(roomId, password);
await client.sendEvent('seek', 10);
const state = await client.waitForState();
expect(state.time).toBe(10);
```

## Mocking

- Mock WebSocket connections for unit tests
- Use in-memory room state for testing (don't require real server)
- Mock time for drift reconciliation tests
- Mock rate limiter for event handler tests

## Test Data

- Use predictable UUIDs for test roomId/clientId
- Use fixed timestamps for deterministic tests
- Clean up test rooms after each test
